  My experience overall is very good .

I generally dont write reviews but it was a very good experience with this duo.

I had severe toothache but the reason was because of wisdom tooth. Doctor suggested to go for extraction.

Firstly when i spoke to Dr. Kavitha and she could sense that I am too scared for any extraction, she comforted me saying that I can just come, get the tooth checked and if i dont wish to continue i can leave it. But not to worry. That itself was too comforting. I decided to go there.

After going there, didn’t have to wait at all.

Dr. Srihari and Dr. Kavitha were have given time quickly. I explained to them that I am too scared of pricks or anything and i tend to faint.

Dr. Srihari has also again comforted me during the whole procedure. I was feeling uncomfortable after first injection and to that he was way too much patient with me.

When he removed the tooth, it took him literally 2-5 min but i think the team spent more than 15 min to make me calm in that place.

I may not have gone ahead if they were not this patient.

I know they have given their valuable time to me and gone extra mile to make me feel comfortable.

Dr. Kavitha has also personally been checking on me after the procedure on the conditions.

I would certainly recommend the duo.

Thanks a lot doctor.

You both are charming

Awsome work and good hospitality  friendly behavior 
Really appreciate the work, i give 100% ratings

I got my wisdom tooth removal from Dr. Srihari. He is very friendly and welcoming. 
Due to hectic schedule and work load, few doctors get frustrated and that leads bad conversation. That i don’t like at all, i don’t visit such doctors again. But Dr Srihari is very nice and he explained all the things to me.

I was very scared for procedure and pain. He make me feel comfortable & assured me i will not get pain. After that only he started the procedure. At each step of procedure he told me what can happen so that i can reach appropriately. Like in case if get pain during procedure, how to signal for same. Its been 6 days and i didn’t got pain even once and that part is healing fast. 
Overall i am very happy with Dr Srihari. Will recommend his to others as well.
Thanks Dr.

Very approachable doctor. His friendly conversation set up the tone for my surgery.
He was crisp in explaining the problem and precise in his work. 
I got my wisdom tooth extracted. So far so good. I don't see any side effects. Neither any swelling nor extreme pain. But that could be very subjective and dependent on body composition and medical history.
One suggestion to the doc though (assuming he is reading this review):
Though tooth extraction may sound minor and very routine to the doctor, ultimately it's a surgical procedure which may involve loss of some amount of blood. It's advisable that the doctor notes down the blood group and any such relevant info before starting the procedure. This was not done in my case and I realized it after I started spitting blood while gargling during the procedure :)

Dr. Srihari was very polite and humble. He explained the process patiently in my mom’s native language. She was very tensed About the procedure. He calmed her down patiently and assured her of speedy recovery. He also gave phone support for any problems after the procedure. Highly recommend this doctor.
